[Purpose] The purpose of this study was to evaluate the amount of physical 
activity of the patients with critical limb ischemia consecutively in order to 
clarify the characteristics of physical activity of critical limb ischemia. 
[Subjects and Methods] Twelve patients who were eligible for the 2 months of 
consecutive evaluation of the amount of physical activity were enrolled in the 
study (men: 11; woman: 1; mean age: 64.4 [range: 44-80]). A pedometer with an 
