walked. There was also no correlation between the number of steps walked and age 
as well as the maximum strength of the knee-extension muscle, skin perfusion 
pressure of the sole and the dorsum, and QOL scores. [Conclusion] The number of 
steps walked of the patients with critical limb ischemia was remarkably low and 
no significant association with health-related QOL.

